	"__INITIAL_DATA__": {"current_talk":66,"comments":{"id":64,"count":4553,"talk_id":66},"description":"Sir Ken Robinson makes an entertaining and profoundly moving case for creating an education system that nurtures (rather than undermines) creativity.","event":"TED2006","language":"en","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-64k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":9605076,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-180k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":26709967,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-320k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":47264296,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"450k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-450k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":66242925,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"600k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-600k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":88106508,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"950k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-950k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":136494946,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"1500k":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-1500k.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":212867024,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"podcast-light":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-light.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":9701571,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"podcast-regular":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":66300280,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"podcast-high":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-480p.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":136601633,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"audio-podcast":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006.mp3?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":7423353,"mime_type":"audio/mp3"},"podcast-low-en":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-low-en.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":26803007,"mime_type":"video/mp4"},"podcast-high-en":{"uri":"https://download.ted.com/talks/SirKenRobinson_2006-480p-en.mp4?apikey=489b859150fc58263f17110eeb44ed5fba4a3b22","filesize_bytes":136750270,"mime_type":"video/mp4"}}},"name":"Ken Robinson: Do schools kill creativity?","slug":"ken_robinson_says_schools_kill_creativity","speakers":[{"id":69,"slug":"sir_ken_robinson","firstname":"Ken","lastname":"Robinson","description":"Author/educator","photo_url":"https://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/1465_254x191.jpg","whatotherssay":"Ken's vision and expertise is sought by public and commercial organizations throughout the world.","whotheyare":"Creativity expert Sir Ken Robinson challenges the way we're educating our children. He champions a radical rethink of our school systems, to cultivate creativity and acknowledge multiple types of intelligence. ","whylisten":"<p>Why don&#39;t we get the best out of people? Sir Ken Robinson argues that it&#39;s because we&#39;ve been educated to become good workers, rather than creative thinkers. Students with restless minds and bodies -- far from being cultivated for their energy and curiosity -- are ignored or even stigmatized, with terrible consequences. <strong>&quot;We are educating people out of their creativity,&quot; Robinson says.</strong> It&#39;s a message with deep resonance. Robinson&#39;s TED Talk has been distributed widely around the Web since its release in June 2006. The most popular words framing blog posts on his talk? &quot;Everyone should watch this.&quot; </p><p>A visionary cultural leader, Sir Ken led the British government&#39;s 1998 advisory committee on creative and cultural education, <strong>a massive inquiry into the significance of creativity in the educational system and the economy</strong>, and was knighted in 2003 for his achievements. His 2009 book, <em><a href=\"http://sirkenrobinson.com/?page_id=15\" target=\"_blank\">The Element: How Finding Your Passion Changes Everything</a></em>, is a&nbsp;<em>New York Times</em> bestseller and has been translated into 21 languages. A 10th anniversary edition of his classic work on creativity and innovation,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sirkenrobinson.com/?page_id=15\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Out of Our Minds: Learning to be Creative</em></a>, was published in 2011. His 2013 book,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sirkenrobinson.com/?page_id=420\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Finding Your Element: How to Discover Your Talents and Passions and Transform Your Life</em></a>, is a practical guide that answers questions about finding your personal Element. In his latest book,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://sirkenrobinson.com/creative-schools-the-grassroots-revolution-thats-transforming-education/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Creative Schools: The Grassroots Revolution That&rsquo;s Transforming Education</em></a>,&nbsp;he argues for an end to our outmoded industrial educational system and proposes a highly personalized, organic approach that draws on today&rsquo;s unprecedented technological and professional resources to engage all students.</p>","title":"Sir","middleinitial":""}],"threadId":64,"url":"https://www.ted.com/talks/ken_robinson_says_schools_kill_creativity","viewed_count":47225779,"talks":[{"comments":64,"corrections":[],"description":"Sir Ken Robinson makes an entertaining and profoundly moving case for creating an education system that nurtures (rather than undermines) creativity.","downloads":{"id":66,"languages":[{"languageName":"Afrikaans","endonym":"Afrikaans","languageCode":"af","ianaCode":"af","isRtl":false},{"languageName":"Albanian","endonym":"S